caption: We really had a good breakfast time! Food was delicious, our waiter was super nice and all Christmas atmosphere was wonderful! I already recommended to my friends who have kids. Thank you for balloons kids were extra happy all day!!!!

This place is amazing. You literally pay for what you drink since you’re your own server. Cocktails, beer, exotic drinks on tap you name it. Not to mention the board games and calming ambiance. Highly recommend you go with 3 or more friends on a cold night for maximum satisfaction.

Absolutely horrible service.  We had a blonde waitress with glasses.  She was absolutely horrible.   Took way to long to take our order.  One night she never brought me my drink.  I had to ask the food server for my drinks.   She seemed to have an attitude like she didnt want to even wait on me.  I am always a polite southern gentleman so maybe she just didnt like southerners.  Anyway her level of service was reflected in her tip.  I expect more from a $400 a night hotel restaurant.   I will make sure not to book my hotel for 2021 FABTECH convention here.
Small menu and high price. Adequate food with large portions.
Good beer, bland vibe
Had high expectations because it looked amazing, but we waited 45 minutes for warm food. Although the food was decent, and slightly overpriced, the service was terrible.

Thought it was absolutely delicious! Stopped in for a beer and a quick bite to eat. The charcuterie board was fantastic. The staff was a little awkward however as they were standing two tables over watching us eat. Almost felt as if we were being rushed to finish and leave although the restaurant was still set to be open for several hours.

I've had drinks in bars from all over the world but never have I had bartender as amazing as Danny. Amazing service, knew what to recommend on everything from sports to video games. And I gotta say he makes the best old fashioned I've ever tasted in my life. Promote this man.

We stopped here for dinner before a show. The charcuterie plate was phenomenal. We had the pork belly and the pan seared chicken breast, both of which were excellent. Our server was friendly and efficient, as was the table busser.

Twelve dollars for a bottled beer you can get at Walgreens and food whose only distinction is that it's priced like The Gage for a third of the quality. Have had better meals at the Whole Foods hot bar near by.

This place was a quick walk from my hotel, so I definitely had to check it out! The fish and chips were fantastic (the grilled lemon wedge was a nice touch) and the Columbus Tap Ale was well worth a second round! Christina sat me a second after I walked in, had my beer on the table a minute later, and even apologized for the food taking so long (all of 5 minutes 😂)! The staff was friendly, food was great, and service was impeccable... I highly recommend this place!
Good drink menu
Great chicken salad... Would be a five star but service was a little slow for a Wednesday afternoon lunch...great spot though

I stopped in for lunch. I had the Seared Scallops with carrot coconut curry, Swiss chard, and roasted baby carrots. The curry was subtle and the whole dish was crazy delicious. I highly recommend it. The lunch atmosphere is casual. Patrons occupied most of the tables, and it was a bit loud for me. I will surely eat there again, but is not the place for a quiet conversation. And that is perfectly ok. Just a heads up.
excellent service.great food.
Our waiter Nick and Chef Rickie were amazing! The atmosphere and food was beyond expectations! I would highly recommend this restaurant to anyone visiting the Chicago area!!
(Translated by Google) Good food, but very high prices, especially for breakfast  (Original) Buon cibo, ma prezzi molto elevati, in particolare per le colazioni

Check your burger to make sure it's cooked the way you want it before you leave. It's not worth getting raw ground chuck when you asked for medium well for the pricing.
Good variety of breakfast food offered. The food from the buffet was a bit cold though
Really good food, good portion sizes, but definitely wouldn't be hard to eat at cheaper places with similar quality
Great service! They steal was cooked perfectly and great beer! The server was attentive and outstanding! A very enjoyable lunch!
Terrible service and they automatically added a 20% service charge because we were a party of five. We got the buffet and their service was still terrible.

We had breakfast here after my sister's wedding. The server was extremely rude to our whole party. We ordered at 9:50am and still didn't  have the food at 10:40am. It was a waffle and one side egg. When we asked if the food would be out soon the lady told us that's why we suggested the buffet. It's unprofessional. I wouldn't recommend this place. The restaurant was not even full, so using the excuse of being busy was absurd.
Service was lackluster which matched the food.    Loud TV and ambient sound but did serve food and drink.   Didnt hate it but less than average and typical high price for hotel restaurant
Decent food and service.  A little pricey for what you recieve.  Also acoustics are poor.  It is very loud with even small groups.
Great food and service is awesome!
Salmon burger was good and tasty.  My Margarita was extremely small for the price.
Expensive
Good selection of beers, break the wallet out though.
Fish and chips were tasty

1. Items were over priced and the food tasted bland. 2. We waited long times for our order to be taken, food to come out,  and for the waiter to see if we needed anything. We were there for an hour and a half and we only ordered two appetizers. 3. It was raining outside and they had the AC going in the restuarant. It was a very unpleasant to have to wait in the cold restaurant.
I had the chef's special of the day, Mediterranean fish with chick peas salad, olive oil and basil. It was super!

For a great hotel, the bar has a lot to be desired...especially the policies.  Full bar but turned on all the lights and kicked everyone out at 11:50. Go next door to Big Bar at Hyatt for late night hospitality.
Great food and Veronica was an amazing server!
Great food
Drinks were nearly $20 each for vodka and soda!
A decent gastropub,  with inspiration cocktails and late night menu(went there after a concert).
A bit over priced as they are part of the Fairmont hotel but the food was good and a fair beer selection.

Here's the thing, even for a hotel restaurant, if Im going to spend $27 on a burger, it should be an awesome burger. It was good, but not amazing or memorable. Tiny drink glasses and skimpy on the refills.
The "tall" glass of wine was mysteriously the same size as the regular but $30 more. Total scam. Be careful.
Expensive.
We had a nice business lunch. I wish they had more vegan options but the grilled veggies were tasty. Loved the asparagus.
Great lunch, meeting and cocktail spot
Great atmosphere
Arranged for a reception there.  Food was excellent, all arrangements were spot on and the servers were excellent.  VERY GOOD  experience.  Highly recommended.
Really nice place, food is great
Very nice
Not great
Food was ok, but very over priced. Service was very good and staff was very attentive.
Great food and drinks. Cheers!
Lot of screens with sports games on. Quick service at the bar even during rush hours of Friday evening

Tried to have breakfast here as guest of the hotel on St Pattys Day. It was understandably busy. We sat at the bar the bartender rolled her eyes at us when we sat down. We had to ask for menus for food. When she took our order she never asked how we wanted our eggs or which options we wanted and was just rude like we were an inconvience to her standing around. After over an hour of waiting for our food and I asked her if she could check on it her response was we are busy if you didn’t notice. And we did notice  at the fact there was an entire new group of people around us with their food and we still didn’t have our food. She continued to make smart remarks and I left they then proceeded to call the police on my 64 year old father and said we were threatening. When I asked to speak with management they were young and dumb with nothing to say. Worst experience of my life and we definitely won’t return to the hotel or their dining.
Good drinks. Good enough bar food.
See Fairmont Hotel for reviews.
Expensive. Limited wine and beer selection.

Yet another concept, crammed into the Fairmont and has no idea as to what it want's to be.  Years ago, I worked at Entre Nous at The Fairmont. There was a phenomenal Italian joint, La Primavera. They were EXCELLENT restaurants.  The food is very nice here, but no real... Drive or INSPIRATION.

Great comfy large tobacco leather seats. Gold trim modern but 80s decor blended into 2019. Hexagon white tile marbled with grey accents. Enthusiastic staff and relax fun atmosphere. You'll have a terrific time here.
Excellent Breakfast, Great service....would go back next time I'm in Chicago

Awesome bar! Wife and I had a couple drinks there recently while staying across the street at the Swisse.  Bartenders have Chicago-Attitude , not a bad thing. I was born in Chicago so I get it, out of towners might be put off. Its a snarky I'll help you but watch your step kinda thing, you gotta be in control of your bar. Stupid folks, wedding parties probably come in and need the tone set.  My wife is a born/bred suburban chick so she thought the bartender hated us. We chatted with him a bit and once he realized we were not douche-bags he treated us like returning regulars. I'd definitely go back, I'd love to see how they deal with real A-Bags! :)

The food is actually pretty good, that would be 4 stars. I usually don't let bad service affect my rating but it was truly just incredibly slow. We thought they forgot about us. Also, it was terribly cold and the vents were blowing out cold air for a while...
Good beer selection and food.
The best staff around!
Great food

Went for lunch and had a Tap Burger and house chips. Chips were poor in taste. Tangy with to much seasoning and had to get the fries which were better. Burger was good. Decent size and tasty but for $21 it was not what I expected.
Food, drinks and service were spot on. Highly recommend. A little loud during busiest hours.
Limited menu and on the higher priced side. Friendly staff and clean facility.
It was interesting

Visited the place for the first time after two years working in the area, well I should have gone to my regular places. The bartender not friendly,  actually looked bothered by my presence.  Then one female server was having a discussion with the bartender and other man about their hours are cut, and they are probably pushing the other server into retirement that conversation took 5 minutes while she was going back and forth.  After placing my order the bartender never checked on me and when I asked for my check he never looked at me or said a thing but he was very nice to the couple next to me telling them to wait one second while he rings my bill. Plain rude and completely unnecessary.  Because the have large varieties of beers.  Expensive? Not at all I mean is downtown Chicago duh! Food? Only tried fries, mediocre but not nasty! Never going back!
Bar tender was friendly. But the drinks were EXPENSIVE! 1 bottle of beer cost more than a six-pack in a store. The food was good, and the wings had a lot of meat in them.

Friendly service!

Food was disappointing. $30 for 3 scallops, bitter fish n' chips. Beer and drink scene was better. Go somewhere else for dinner.
Fish and chips are good and great beer selections
Very hearty and delicious fish and chips. Top off with great dark ale.
Standard hotel bar.  Good selection of local beers.
Nice dinner I had a good time, they might of done to much to that tap burger but it was good

This was a wonderful place to eat. The look is clean without being cold. I am from out of state and my server Elizabeth made me feel welcome and made a great suggestion for dinner. We got scallops and short ribs for dinner and both were excellent thanks to the chef. I go home tomorrow with warm memories and a warm belly.
good food and great drinks

The signature wings are amazing! Craft beer selection is on point. Thanks to my server Elizabeth! Staff was as delightful as the food. Columbus Tap is doing it right. Will definitely be back.
Best chicken noodle soup so far
Great location, good food but service can be extremely slow at times especially with parties of more than four.
Good food and a good time.  Was a bit.of a wait to get in.

My husband and I came into Chicago for our 10 year anniversary and we had a few issues during the stay, but Gia remember our drinks from 2 nights prior. She had amazing customer service!! For having a rough start to our actual anniversary evening events with the hotel, she made things 10 times better. And when we came back to the hotel for the evening, Gia had requested tiramisu and strawberries to be left in our room! Thank you so much Gia!  We appreciate you're perfect customer service relationship!

I really liked this place. Great location near millennium park and the Chicago river walk. The food menu was amazing. Such interesting and unique dishes... it was honestly really difficult to decide. If you are a beer lover, this place is definitely for you!

This is a business lunch joint. A good one at that because it wasn't too crowded and noisy so people can talk easier. On the food, I had a beet salad. How I read the menu was more of an arugula salad with lots of those small white slices of beets. It was actually, literally, sq inch cubes of red beets, topped with a tiny arugula salad. Beets themselves tasted like beets. However if you have it together with the arugula fixing, it's as good tasting as beets will get, and I'm sure that's what the chef intended.
Good atmosphere and beer selection, but mediocre food and sub-par service, especially at the bar.
Clean and modern with good food and drinks, but souless.  Good for guests haard sell for chicagoans
Great salmon salad
Staff was super friendly, but the food and wine prices were bad... very misconstrued
Good food and beer. You can get your growler filled!
Went to the bar. Nice place for a quick drink. Good atmosphere.
Easy to walk in for lunch, nice big bar, great tasting chicken salad for price/size. Relaxed vibe. Worth stopping by.

Great food, albeit slow, with some mixed service experiences. The server was friendly enough to make up for the host's shortcomings, but everything did run slowly and for no apparent reason. The carrot soup and roasted fingerlings are quite good.
Fun place. Good selection of beers on tap.
Although the food selection is limited, the options available are delicious!
Yummy Prime rib sandwich. Friendly staff, great beer selection, outlets under the bar for bonus points!
Save your money and appetite for somewhere better. Overpriced, overvalued, below average food.
Food and service are excellent along with nice beer selection.  My only suggestion is menu could use a lite more variety.
Large portions, great food and atmosphere.
Amazing food
The food was great!
Excellent Po-Boy Sandwich and salad

I have been here several times since it opened, and I am so excited to have a new option for work-related lunches, dinners and drinks! I enjoy their dynamic menu with imaginative options, such as avocado toasts, barbecued cauliflower and pub cheese with veggies. Their menu items are a breath of fresh air compared to the typical restaurants in the area, which serve the same-old burgers, sandwiches, fries and cheese curds. Wish they had more competitive drink specials or a happy hour.
While in Chicago my wife and I ate here twice. We loved the menu and the staff was curtious​ and quick.
very good price for the meal. very delicious. our waiter was a bit odd.  the waiters wore strange clothes. but great food/atmosphere/location for a quick-ish moderately priced bite

We came in during restaurant week before a Broadway in Chicago show. Service was great. Food portions seemed a bit off for prix fixe menu. Soup appetizer was delicious but very small while a salad appetizer was gigantic. The deconstructed smores dessert was AMAZING. I cannot convey how good this was. Great beer list, great wine list. This is a nice after work place that doesn't feel like it is part of a hotel or a happy hour scene.
This is a nice, open and airy pub inside the Fairmont Hotel.  The service was friendly and the drinks did not disappoint.
The food was delicious and the hot chocolate taste really good

Nonchalant staff (2 different crews) that added fries (extra 2$) to my burger order not once but on two different days without asking me. Once is a mistake, twice is systemic I will solve it by not returning there. Unbefitting of a Fairmont.

I walked in from the street at around 10:45 pm for a quick beer with some friends. The host stand at the hotel entrance was the only one open and the hostess was busy, so it took us a few minutes to get seated. The hostess got us water immediately and we then waited close to 20 minutes for our waitress, Elizabeth. She was one of two waitresses with a decent crowd for a Saturday night. After taking our drink orders, she brought one of our party the wrong beer and didn't check back with us until it was already too late. She did split the checks for us, but rolled her eyes and scoffed at my tip. I can't comment on the food, but the only reason this didn't get 1 star is because it does have a good beer selection. I definitely will not be returning to this place ever.

Visited the Columbus Tap on a work lunch. Service was expedient, if not distant and busy - not very sociable staff. We enjoyed the Jumbo Pretzels and Chicken Wings as an appetizer. The pretzels were good and came with both a cheese sauce and house-made dijon honey mustard dip. The chicken wings were underwhelming - baked and encrusted with what could be described as kin to barbecue potato chip crumbs - however I may be missing something more refined palates would enjoy. I ordered the Wild Mushroom Bisque as well as Fish and Chips. The Bisque was tasty, quite enjoyable, however a larger serving would have been liked for the price ($8). The Fish and Chips were delicious, fried perfectly and lightly, however there was too little house-made tartar sauce provided for my tastes. The fries were unmemorable and I did not finish them. Overall, the atmosphere is comfortable and is perfect for meeting lunches and other outings. I would not personally visit again due to the prices charged for what you get.
Good food (rotisserie chicken is excellent) and a very good list of beers and spirits.

The bartender was overwhelmed by a modest crowd and it took her forever to take a beer order. Then I placed an order for a burger medium RARE (yes, I annunciated RARE) with ONLY bacon and cheese (also loudly and clearly annunciated).  The first burger arrived with an announcement of "Medium" burger. I promptly returned it for a medium rare one, which arrived with all the toppings, not only bacon and cheese. I pushed this one across the counter along with the remainder of my beer and walked out without paying. At this time of night it was too late to get dinner elsewhere and they should have paid me.  DO NOT EAT HERE.

Listen to the reviews for this restaurant and DO NOT waste your time. It is trying so hard to be hipster and falls short. It's pathetic. They opened a sparkling water for me without asking if I wanted it and charged me NINE DOLLARS.  There are so many places to eat in this city, do not waste a meal here.
Upscale gastropub in the Fairmont Hotel. Delicious appetizers, including healthy options, as well as locally-themed cocktails, and a variety of beers.
